# Windows Server Administrative Shortcuts (.msc) Reference Guide

A quick reference sheet for essential Windows Server management consoles and tools. These shortcuts can be executed via the **Run dialog (Win + R)**, **PowerShell**, or **Command Prompt**.

---

## 🔐 Active Directory & Identity
*   **`dsa.msc`** – Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)
*   **`adsiedit.msc`** – ADSI Edit (Advanced AD Object Editor)
*   **`domain.msc`** – Active Directory Domains and Trusts
*   **`gpmc.msc`** – Group Policy Management Console
*   **`dssite.msc`** – Active Directory Sites and Services

## 🖥️ Core Infrastructure Services
*   **`dnsmgmt.msc`** – DNS Manager
*   **`dhcpmgmt.msc`** – DHCP Manager
*   **`certsrv.msc`** – Certification Authority (CA)
*   **`virtmgmt.msc`** – Hyper-V Manager
*   **`iscsicpl.exe`** – iSCSI Initiator Configuration

## ⚙️ System & Server Management
*   **`compmgmt.msc`** – Computer Management (Shared Folders, Local Users, etc.)
*   **`services.msc`** – Windows Services
*   **`diskmgmt.msc`** – Disk Management
*   **`eventvwr.msc`** – Event Viewer (Logs)
*   **`taskschd.msc`** – Task Scheduler
*   **`cluadmin.msc`** – Failover Cluster Manager

## 🌐 Network & IIS
*   **`ncpa.cpl`** – Network Connections (IP Configuration)
*   **`inetmgr`** – Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager
*   **`wf.msc`** – Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security
